node.text:
Watch is NOW on iTunes, On Demand, and select theaters 🎭 

Two FBI agents cross paths with Crawford, a Florida cop who's investigating a string of murders that appear to be related. When an undercover sting goes horribly wrong, Crawford soon finds himself in a twisted game of cat and mouse with the killer.

With @meganfox @machinegunkelly @emilehirsch @reallycaitlinxox @oliveabercrombie @lukashaas

Watch this Psychological Thriller on iTunes and On Demand 🔥

Actors: #dylanobrien @maikamonroe @amandabrugel #hannahgross @keirgilchristofficial #emorycohen #liisarepomartell #ad #Flashbackmovie
#Flashbackmovie2021

node.text:
This is the question that I ask myself before I go to bed. I plan out part of my day by listing the top three things that I want to complete. In doing so, when you wake up the next day, you have a plan of action... you're not trying to figure out what you need to do at 5am. 

Having three things that you want to complete will also keep you accountable. It helps you avoid the to-do list that never ends and it will feel great when you complete your list.

As a result, the next day you will be ready to complete your top three things and this will continue to carry over to the next day and so on.

What are three things you can complete tomorrow? Comment them below and come back to let me know when you've checked them off!

Make sure you follow @nelygalan for more tips of the trade 💯👇

@nelygalan 
@nelygalan 

#accountabilitypartner
#stayfocused
#mujeresemprendedoras
#womenempoweringwomen

node.text:
What do you see?

According to theory we are either left-brain or right-brain dominant.

“If you’re mostly analytical and methodical in your thinking, you’re said to be left-brained. If you tend to be more creative or artistic, you’re thought to be right-brained.

The left brain is more verbal, analytical, and orderly than the right brain. It’s sometimes called the digital brain. It’s better at things like reading, writing, and computations.

According to dated research, the left brain is also connected to:

logic
sequencing
linear thinking
mathematics
facts
thinking in words

The right brain is more visual and intuitive. It’s sometimes referred to as the analog brain. It has a more creative and less organized way of thinking.

Dated research suggests the right brain is also connected to:

imagination
holistic thinking
intuition
arts
rhythm
nonverbal cues
feelings visualization
daydreaming”

Comment below what you see and if according to this, it’s accurate 💯
#MotivationMafia
